value.value: A measurement of the ability of erythrocytes to change shape without rupturing, as they pass through narrow spaces, such as the microvasculature.
A colorectal adenoma which develops independently more than six months after the removal of a previous colorectal adenoma.

Quantification of visual masking, a phenomenon of visual perception which occurs when the visibility of one image, called a target, is reduced by the presence of another, called a mask. Timing arrangements include forward masking, backward masking, and simultaneous masking. Spatial arrangements include pattern masking and metacontrast. Visual masking deficits are potential schizophrenia endophenotypes.

Autoimmune neurological syndromes (AINS) with autoantibodies against the 65kDa isoform of glutamic acid decarboxylase (GAD65). It can present with three clinical syndromes that can partially overlap: limbic encephalitis with seizures or epilepsy, cerebellitis with ataxia, and stiff-person-syndrome. Anti-GAD65 autoantibodies also characterize autoimmune diabetes mellitus (type 1A).
Quantification or estimate of cardiovascular age, e.g. as derived from electrocardiograms (ECGs) or biomarkers.
Quantification of the volume of the fornix.
Quantification of the space between a blood vessel and the brain's pia mater. It may be measured by magnetic resonance imaging as an imaging marker of cerebral small vessel disease.
